				posted 2004-10-07 01:21&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=11098"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=11097"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	&quot; this may sound really supid but how do you attack (or how do you seige a planet)?<br />
also what concentration should i begin in? reasearch?<br />
and should i get planets by expeditions or attacking? at what power should i start attacking often?<br />
is it better to have lots of fleets with less or weaker ships or less fleets but more or more powerful ships in them?<br />
thx 4 the help&quot;<br />
<br />
--------------------------------------<br />
1) you can attack people by (a) declaring war on people in your own council through the diplomacy menu (click 'send message', choose a person, choose 'Declare war' and send it) or (b) attacking any players in range with whom your council is at war with. Speakers declare war, or your council may be declared upon by another council. at any rate, all players in the council show up on the 'siege' menu and you can attack them, as do any players you have declared war on personally who are in your range. <br />
<br />
2) You could go into research mode, it depends on whether you get enough PP and fast enough ship building..i tend to stay in blanaced the majority of the time, sometimes switching when i want more production here or there...but make sure to set some plants to build a lot of labs, as they are what makes research faster...i suggest putting them on crappy planets so you can blow the planet up when research is done.<br />
<br />
3) At the start, get planets from expedition until you are able to produce enough money and fast enough ship building times to be able to produce the fleets needed to attack other players...that mins a minimum of cruiser size ships but bigger the better<br />
<br />
4) there is no set 'power' when you should start attacking players..it is more based on whether you have good enough ships, and whether their fleets are weaker then yours...if there are other players around you with similar power and more planets they tend to be better targets....<br />
<br />
5) It is generally better to have less fleets with much more powerful ships. In the start it is best to just mass produce fusion cruisers or other ships, since other people around you will have the same weapons and building times generally, so whoever builds the most and attacks with more ships wins. As you get more research and faster ship building, you want to build bigger ships with better weapons, even if they take longer to build. I have lost count of how many times I attacked a guy with 2 ships and beat his 50 or 60 because mine was 2 dreadnaughts with good weapons against 60 cruisers with slightly worse weapons.<br />
<br />
Houston<br />
Canadian Right			   <P align=right></P>
